<p>Make an index</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/62056/whats-the-easiest-way-to-make-a-list-of-most-common-words-in-a-list</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Make a text document into a list of words .txt?</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>cat *.txt | printf '%s\n' $(cat *.txt) | sort | uniq -c | sort -gr | less 
</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>First get rid of Punctuation and Pipe ‘</td>
          <td>’</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>cat *.txt | tr '[:punct:]' ' ' | tr '|' ' ' | printf '%s\n' $(cat *.txt) | sort | uniq -c | sort -gr | less
</code></pre></div></div>

:ET